The paper discusses the use of bibliometric indicators in research assessment exercises, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on the Italian VQR 2011-2014 exercise, which evaluated research output in various disciplines, including computer science. The use of citation and journal metrics to grade publications is relevant to sub-categories such as digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
